                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><p>A marble plaque, missing the upper left corner, and with part of the surviving upper section also broken but still attached. The upper, left and right edges are straight, but the lower edge very uneven. Traces of mortar around the edges. The letters show extensive traces of red rubrication. The rear is finished smooth. A label on the reverse reads 'S. Giovanni 2014'.</p>
                                    <material ana="#material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble" type="stone.marble" subtype="unverified" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html">marble</material>
                                    <objectType ana="#object.plaque" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259">plaque</objectType>
                                    <dimensions>
                                        <height unit="cm">21.5</height>
                                        <width unit="cm">26</width>
                                        <depth unit="cm">1.7-2.2</depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </support>
                                <condition ana="#condition.damaged"/>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout><p>Four lines of text, filling the upper part of the plaque, and tending to slant upwards across each line. A Staurogram is inserted between the first two lines of text.</p>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</rs>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.rubrication.red">Rubrication, red</rs>
                                    <damage ana="#text_condition.incomplete"/>
                                </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><p>Letters of somewhat irregular size and form. Alpha of cursive form, lunate epsilon and sigma, uncial omega, omicron of varying form.</p>
                                <locus from="line1" to="line1">Line 1-1</locus>
